Prerequisites
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

clive >= 2.0.0 (http://clive.sf.net)
Perl >= 5.8 (http://perl.org)

clivefeed
---------

* Config::Tiny/2.12           * WWW::Curl/4.05
* XML::RSS::LibXML/0.3002     * Clipboard/0.09
* Tk/804.027                  * URI::Escape/3.29
* Tk::DialogBox/4.013         * HTML::Strip/1.06
* Tk::FontDialog/0.15         * Tk::Tree/4.005

clivescan
---------

* Config::Tiny/2.12           * WWW::Curl/4.05
* Tk/804.027                  * Tk::Tree/4.005
* Tk::DialogBox/4.013         * Clipboard/0.09
* Tk::FontDialog/0.15         * HTML::TokeParser/2.37

clivepass
---------

* Crypt::PasswdMD5/1.3        * Crypt::Twofish2/1.01
* Crypt::Salt/0.01            * Config::Tiny/2.12

Most distros should have the above versions available as packages.
If not, you can still use CPAN to install the missing modules, e.g.:
    % cpan install WWW::Curl # as root


Installation
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Extract:
    % tar xvjf clive-utils-$release.tar.bz2; cd clive-utils-$release

Run:
    # If the path to clive(1) is not specified (e.g. --clive=path), the
    # clive-utils programs try to locate it in the $PATH.

    % clivefeed [option]... [URL]...
    % clivescan [option]... [URL]...
    % clivepass [option]...

Getting started:
    % clivefeed --manual
    % clivescan --manual
    % clivepass --manual

The manual pages is written in Perl Pod markup language and they are embedded
in the script files. See "perldoc perlpod" for more info. For example:
    % pod2man clivefeed > clivefeed.1

See also:
    configs/ subdir for example configuration files


Installation: FreeBSD (7.0)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

From the ports:
  * x11-toolkits/p5-Tk-FontDialog
  * textproc/p5-XML-RSS-LibXML
  * security/p5-Digest-SHA
  * devel/p5-Config-Tiny
  * x11-toolkits/p5-Tk
  * www/p5-HTML-Parser
  * www/p5-HTML-Strip
  * net/p5-URI
  * ftp/curl
  * security/p5-Crypt-PasswdMD5
  * security/p5-Crypt-Twofish2
  * security/p5-Crypt-Salt
  * security/p5-Digest-MD5
  * converters/p5-MIME-Base64
  * devel/p5-File-Path
  -- Optional:
  * x11/p5-Clipboard

From CPAN:
  * WWW::Curl


Installation: Ubuntu (Hardy)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

From apt: # Typically: "sudo apt-get install $module"
  * libcurl4-openssl-dev
  * libhtml-parser-perl
  * libconfig-tiny-perl
  * libdigest-sha-perl
  * libfile-spec-perl
  * liburi-perl 
  * perl-doc
  * perl-tk
  * libmd5-perl
  * libemail-mime-encodings-perl
  * libio-all-perl
  -- Optional:
  * xclip (for Clipboard module below)

From CPAN: # Typically: "sudo cpan install $module"
  * WWW::Curl
  * HTML::Strip
  * XML::RSS::LibXML
  * Tk::FontDialog
  * Crypt::PasswdMD5
  * Crypt::Twofish2
  * Crypt::Salt
  -- Optional:
  * Clipboard
